pr_title: Updated service file to solve error
pr_body:
Current Behaviour: On starting the service file the following error occurs:
`Failed to start augur_view.service: Unit augur_view.service has a bad unit file setting`. and the log shows: 

`Neither a valid executable name nor an absolute path`
`Unit configuration has fatal error, unit will not be started.`

Solution and changes made:

- Updating the service file adding absolute path of directory to ExecStart.
- Corrected a typo

The systemd docs make clear that the executable must either be an absolute path, or a simple program name. Since we are assuming Gunicorn will not be installed at the system level, we must direct the user to provide the absolute path to their gunicorn executable in the virtual environment.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 6, 22, 8, 27, 31, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Ulincsys', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 903491456, 'comment_body': "Yes right, I will correct that. Should I just change the statement to: 
'First argument will be the absolute path to the Gunicorn executable, which is installed within the virtual environment.' ? 

", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 6, 22, 9, 13, 24, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'Priya730', 'type': 'User'}]

pr_title: augur user add cli commands fixed
pr_body:
Signed-off-by: Priya Srivastava <shivikapriya730@gmail.com>

**Description**
- The changes were required as the current work does not import User model, engine sessions and admin flag does not match with the current schema. Command now also requires firstname and lastname arguments.

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/60316903/188298985-8544b47f-e5b6-49a5-9284-36fd5fe56bf5.png)

<!-- NOTE: **admin attribute not present in the current schema** -->
This PR fixes:
1. Imported engine and User., session fixed.
2. Changed echo message

**Notes for Reviewers**
This PR is continues the changes made by #1912

**Signed commits**
- [x] Yes, I signed my commits.
